  "serviceNotes": {
    "brake fluid": "Brake fluid is hygroscopic and absorbs moisture over time, reducing its boiling point and braking effectiveness. Replacement is time-based, not distance-based \u2014 typically every 2 years regardless of mileage.",
    "check brake pads": "Brake pad thickness is monitored via CBS wear sensors and inspection at scheduled services; 30,000 km is a reasonable inspection cadence between major services. Strong regen on BEV often extends pad life; inspections still required.",
    "coolant flush": "High-voltage battery and e-drive cooling circuit: BMW publishes time/distance-based coolant service for EVs; 60,000 km is a planning proxy\u2014interval estimated, confirm official service data.",
    "gearbox fluid": "Reduction gear / drive unit fluid: officially often \"lifetime\"; 100,000 km mfr row is interval estimated for long-term wear metals in oil\u2014specialist preventive change.",
    "micro filter": "Microfilter replacement per BMW iX EU maintenance information; 20,000 km is a common planning interval\u2014verify CBS and regional booklet."
  },
